-- AmEx profit rises 9 pct on higher card spending
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Tue Jul 29, 2014 04:10PM EDT
-- None



July 29 (Reuters) - American Express Co <AXP.N> reported a 9 percent rise in quarterly profit as more customers used its credit cards in a recovering U.S. economy.

Net income rose to $1.53 billion, or $1.43 per share, for the second quarter ended June 30, from $1.41 billion, or $1.27 per share, a year earlier.